<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>643650</id>
	<title>Unresponsive script warning only appears once</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">If you load a page which brings up the unresponsive script warning, "Stop script" and reload the same page, then the second time will just hang Firefox and not trigger the warning dialog.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.2">1 Load page known to trigger the unresponsive script warning.</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.3">2 Click "Stop script" when warning dialog appears.</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.4">3 Reload same page and wait for warning dialog to appear again.</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.5">4 Force-quit Firefox because dialog does not show up.</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.6">Actual Results:</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.7">Firefox hangs on the unresponsive script after the second page load.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">Expected Results:  
Firefox should display the unresponsive script dialog.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
